							<div class="comment odd" id="c123628">
								<p>I love sloppy joes. This was a favorite when we were growing up. But I was 16 before I learned that Sloppy Joes didn't have beans in them!  My mother in an effort to stretch the budget to feed 4 large appetite kids, use to add a couple of cans of pork and beans to the meat.  Got use to them this way and I still prefer to add the beans to the meat.  A good way to stretch a budget, or just cut back on red meat intake and not cut the protein.  One person commented that her husband wouldn't eat ground beef, they are also great with ground turkey, chicken, or pork and Pork and beans of course!</p>	
