							<div class="comment odd" id="c124240">
								<p>Hmmmmmm...sloppy joes.  My mom used to make them from one of those packaged mixes, Lawry's I think.  And we did the same for our kids.  This was an excellent rendition of an old classic.  I toasted the buns under the broiler, spooned on the meat mixture, topped the mixture with some shredded cheddar cheese, and popped it under the broiler again for a few minutes.  Delicious!  My family tried to pick them up and eat them with their hands but I wimped out and used a fork.  We will never use a packaged mix again to make sloppy joes.  My favorite sloppy joe recipe is one from my Weber Big Book of Grilling cookbook that uses a whole boneless beef chuck roast that is cooked indirectly on the grill and then diced to make the sloppy joes.  However it takes a lot more work and time.</p>	
